    Log on (was camped in KC), Try to get a group in KC, its packed with about 50 players.  Move on to Velkators Lab, Its Crammed to the limit at 48.  Next Spot, Sebillis 67 there tonight on The Rathe (No Raids in progress).  Move AGAIN to Fungus Groove (im down about 300 plat now paying for ports), theres almost 50 there.  I Talk to my guild, Chardok is packed, theres even 24 people in Howling Stones (Thats gotta be a record for a non-raid in Charasis on the Rathe anyhow).   The point of this whole post is, Verant was headed in the right direction with the revamp of The lost temple of Cazic Thule by making a zone with high levels in mind to get them out of some of the places that people are leveling in that still arent 60, The problem is people want safe fast xps (even after they are 60) and with the current configuartion it may be fast xps and great loot but its FAR from safe.  The whole Alt Xps thing is really packing some of the zones that were overused before but now its just getting out of hand, can anyone say &quot;Old School Lower Guk?&quot;  Any suggeestions to alliveate this problem?  I have none except for more zone revamps, which are slow to come in and take ahwile for people to accept.  Thoughts? Ideas? Flames?<br>
