</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umakabrei.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Makabrei</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/27/02 12:02:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23055.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Overcrowding In High Level Camp Zones...Solutions?</span><hr size=1> Dynamic content would be the best way to handle it in my opinion. The life cycle of a high level zone is thus.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>     First group of players zone in and take first impressions.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>     Results... </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>     A</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->&quot;Dude, there is some phat lewts here. Get the guild!&quot;<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>     B</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->&quot;Dude! These mobs are totally kicking our ass and we aren't gettin phat lewts! This sucks, im leaving!&quot;<br>
<br>
If the result is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>     B</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> then we end up with a zone like Charasis. Its a great zone, a really tough one but it does have some nice loot and exp. The risk how ever often out weighs the reward and we end up with a lesser explored zone.<br>
If the result is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>     A</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> then we end up with a Seb. The risk is far out weighed by the reward. Masses of players swarm into the zone and people begain to ignore the lesser explored zone like we see in option <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>     B</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> becase there is an easier alternative. This increase of population decreases the risk further, by making Rezs, crs and other player based assistance easily available.<br>
<br>
This causes the over population that we see today. This over population eventually causes a massive influx of the phat lewts and thus decreases their values, which has all sorts of natsy effects on the economy... which i wont go into. Suffice to say that the poor implementation of the risk vs reward ideals result in an over population and thus an over exploitation of a zone. I propose that verant have a special team specifically for monitoring these problem zones that fit either situation <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>     A</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> or <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>     B</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> and update these zones every few months, changing their content <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>      DRASTICALLY </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> so that the over exploitation can not occur.<br>
<br>
The best changes would be a fluxuation between Risk &gt; Reward, Risk = Reward and Risk &lt; Reward. That way the zone never settles into a label as easy, medium or hard. Keep the players guessing as to what may be around the corner. The game gets tooooo easy if player A can know if he shoots that frog it will bring 3 others and one of them may drop a croaking dirk. Imagine how much more thoughtfull that player would be if he had NO idea how many frogs were gunna come if he shot his arrow... alternativly think about how angcious that player is going to be to find out what those frogs will drop. =)<br>
<br>
To some extent verant has done this... but its too little and too far in between.<br>
<br>
I mean, these changes could be done with simple scripting... based off the time of month. the second week all mobs would drop off loot table 2 instead of loot table 3. Aswell they could have thier levels multiplied by 1.2 making them significantly more difficult... simple scripts could be put in place to keep a zone challenging. All that would be neccesary is a stealthy replacment of a script just when players thought they had it figured out....  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umakabrei.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Makabrei</A> at: 3/27/02 12:12:46 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ueuripedmoped.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Euriped Moped</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/27/02 1:34:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23055.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~yolora/zdance.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Overcrowding In High Level Camp Zones...Solutions?</span><hr size=1> Pops should be dependant on people in zone.<br>
