The amount of experience you earn should be dependant on your skill, not some fugly long timer. So, if 20 people are in the zone.. pops are say 6 minutes. If 40, then pops are 2 minutes. If 100, then pops are 1 minute. Like that..<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umakabrei.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Makabrei</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/27/02 1:38:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23055.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Overcrowding In High Level Camp Zones...Solutions?</span><hr size=1> That would cause exploitations. Farming would become too easy. Uber guilds would just zone in and take over. Then they could AoE everything down and pocket all the phat lewts. Systems that are predictable create a static world. Static worlds are too easily conqured. It makes the game predictable, people will choose things that are predictable and easy to accomplish when given the option. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umakabrei.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Makabrei</A> at: 3/27/02 1:40:53 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaraxasxev.showPublicProfile?language=EN>araxas xev</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/27/02 1:59:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23055.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Overcrowding In High Level Camp Zones...Solutions?</span><hr size=1> 150 in seb? wtf?<br>
