<br>
I personally like madiens eye or the grey. the exp is lower but the groups are way more casual on busy night.  If you can get 2 groups together, western wastes is not bad but you can get into issues with cr. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uweoden.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Weoden</A> at: 3/27/02 2:33:15 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unortherner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Northerner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/27/02 3:27:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23055.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.shaw.ca/sjgardner/Images/celeris2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Overcrowding In High Level Camp Zones...Solutions?</span><hr size=1> The problem really is not so much where to hunt with a group (in my opinion) it is where to go looking for a group.  <br>
<br>
If I have a group of friends, presuming one can port or we are all nearish a Nexus spire, then our options are many.  If I log in and most of my friends are hunting already or raiding or whatever then I am looking for a pickup group.  That's pretty darned common really.  Where will I look for that group?  Likely Velk's, OS or Chardok.<br>
<br>
Sure it is a problem but I don't see easy solutions.  The Nexus ports help but you can't just bop from zone to zone all the time.  It is much like the agreed apon auction areas, momentum has it's sway.  Looking back to even the pre-Kunark days of Gukfest, it is likely better to sit and /lfg a while in a crowded zone than to sit waiting for a potential healer to round out a cobbled together group in ME.  At least once you do get into a decent group in a decent place the exp moves forward.  <br>
<br>
AAexp also really affected this hard but that is another discussion perhaps.  Placing a large number of level 60s back into the experience grind had a massive impact that is still falling out.  Even ignoring AE groups, two 60 Monks can handle what was a pair of camps in Sol B and each pair of 60 (or dual-boxed melees) in Velk's can account for what would be a nice hunting ground for a full group of 50ish people.  The competition is increased hugely while the profitable p/u hunting grounds have not really done so.  This has made for the old horror story of safe and overcamped areas where grinding out halfway acceptible exp is a best-case scenerio.  Ah well, I refuse to get too down about it, the game is still an awful lot of fun when I get to play =)<br>
<br>
(N.B. This does seem to affect non-solo classes more than others of course but thus is the life.) <p><center><b><font color=RED><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=78504>Celeris Tujimson</a><br>Blackguard of The Nameless<br>
