<br>
Lets say we are taking the average over the past 30 minutes, and we are hunting in KC.  When the zone is empty things are on a 6 min timer (i think).  With 20 ppl in the zone, a 6 min timer will keep everyone supplied with mobs.  Each mob would probably be living 5-6 minutes, on average, before being killed.  (I haven't done the math to figure out if 5-6 mins is correct, but this is just an example.)  As the zone gets more crowded, the average time that each mobs lives will decrease.  At this point the system should decrease the spawn time proportionately.  So, with 40 ppl in zone, mobs would be living 3-4 minutes, and the system should decrease the respawn time from 6 minutes to 4 minutes.  Of course, the exact times and averages would have to be tweaked to balance things, but I think the principle is sound.<br>
<br>
There is the age old problem of controlling the rate at which items enter the game, but this can be addressed by having the system spawn named mobs using only the static timers.  For example, in both the cases of a 3 minute and 6 minute average mob lifetimes, named/special mobs could only have a chance of spawning every 6 minutes.  Personally, I don't see the harm in making the named spawn rate scale with the lifetime, since the group is doing more work.  (That and the fact that most non uber mob loots have been farmed to death already.)  A similar system could be implemented to modify the loot tables of mobs spawned on the dynamic timer, to make them drop less.<br>
<br>
Either way, this will give more xp to the players and generally make the game more enjoyable.  It may or may not increase the flow of loots into the game, depending on how it is implemented.  <br>
<br>
Just a though,<br>
Modus <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukanehda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kanehda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/27/02 8:25:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23055.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: overcrowding</span><hr size=1> aren't they opening PoP to help solve this problem <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umithrilsboy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mithrilsboy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/27/02 8:38:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23055.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: overcrowding</span><hr size=1> Maidens Eye <br>
